# Online courses

In this fact sheet, we are going to discuss good quality online courses in applied statistics.

## Contents

- [Semester courses, written content](#semester_written)
- [Long courses, video content](#semester_video)
- [Short resources, video content](#short_video)
- [Software focused](#courses_software)
    - [Implementation in R](#courses_r)
    - [Implementation in Stata](#courses_stata)
- [References](#courses_ref)

## <a class=anchor id=semester_written></a> Semester courses, written content

[Introduction to probability theory](https://online.stat.psu.edu/stat414/). Provided by Penn State University.
[Regression methods](https://online.stat.psu.edu/stat501/). Provided by Penn State University.
[Applied multivariate statistical analysis](https://online.stat.psu.edu/stat505/). Provided by Penn State University.
[Epidemiological research methods](https://online.stat.psu.edu/stat507/). Provided by Penn State University.
[Applied regression analysis](https://online.stat.psu.edu/stat462/). Provided by Penn State University. The production values are not as high for this course.
[OpenIntro Stats](https://www.openintro.org/book/os/). An online textbook with a learning community - parts of it look to be free but there may be a fee involved.
[CAST](https://cast.idems.international/). Provided by Massey University, New Zealand, this resource is used in the SSN online courses but it has not been updated since 2019.

## <a class=anchor id=semester_video></a> Long courses, video content

[Crash course statistics] (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zouPoc49xbk&list=PL8dPuuaLjXtNM_Y-bUAhblSAdWRnmBUcr). A series of 45 10 minute Youtube videos.
[StatQuest](https://www.youtube.com/user/joshstarmer). Sets of 10 - 30 minute Youtube videos grouped around key statistical topics.
[Statistical rethinking](https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCNJK6_DZvcMqNSzQdEkzvzA/videos). A semester of video lectures delivered by Richard McElreath, who wrote the book "Statistical Rethinking" (available at ANU library in hard copy and electronic).
[Wild about Statistics](https://www.youtube.com/c/WildAboutStatistics?app=desktop). A full semester of videos for first year undergraduates delivered by Chris Wild.

##<a class=anchor id=short_video></a> Short resources, video content

[Statistics Learning Centre](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8S5lQWTpujI). videos on introductory statistics content aimed more at high school students. Much of this devloper's material has gone behind a paywall but ou may still stumble across individual videos. 

